{ The Tarrasch Variation of the French doesn't come close to matching the sharp, tactical positions of the Winawer. It instead provides a more strategic and positional game. So while the Winawer includes plenty of attacking sacrifices, the Tarrasch has many positional sacrifices. }
1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nd2 Nf6 4. e5 Nfd7 5. Bd3 (5. f4 c5 6. c3 Nc6 7. Ndf3 Qb6 8. g3 cxd4 9. cxd4 Bb4+ 10. Kf2 f6 11. Kg2 O-O 12. Bd3 Kh8 13. Ne2 fxe5 14. fxe5 Rxf3 15. Kxf3 Nxd4+ 16. Kg2) 5... c5 6. c3 Nc6 7. Ne2 cxd4 8. cxd4 f6 9. exf6 (9. Nf4 Nxd4 10. Qh5+ Ke7 11. exf6+ (11. Ng6+ hxg6 12. exf6+ Nxf6 13. Qxh8 Kf7) 11... Nxf6 12. Ng6+ hxg6 13. Qxh8 Kf7) 9... Nxf6 10. Nf3 Bd6 11. O-O O-O { [%cal Gc1g5,Gg5h4,Gh4g3] } (11... Qc7 12. Bg5 (12. g3 O-O 13. Bf4 Ng4 14. Rc1 Bxf4 15. Nxf4 Rxf4 16. gxf4 Qxf4) 12... O-O 13. Bh4 Nh5 14. Qc2 h6 15. Bh7+ Kh8 16. Bg6 Rxf3 17. Bxh5 (17. gxf3) 17... Bxh2+ 18. Kh1 Rf5 19. Bg6 Bd6 20. Bxf5 exf5) 12. Bf4 Bxf4 13. Nxf4 Ne4 14. Ne2 (14. g3 Ng5 15. Ne5 Nxe5 16. dxe5 Rxf4 17. gxf4) 14... Rxf3 15. gxf3 Ng5 *


